* for autobuilder, use a maintainer format like: 
    CPAN Autobuilder <cpan@example.com>

* you don't need the 'Replaces: core' if installing to SITE
    only for VENDOR
    and only if $(TMP)/usr/bin is non-empty


* cpan-libcgi-perl is not properly parsed from CGI.pm the release
* run 'perl Makefile.PL' for Test fails using cpanp-run-perl
* Have module::build available!

